  "notes": "Standard Moroccan Amazigh / Tamazight (ⵜⴰⵎⴰⵣⵉⵖⵜ ⵜⴰⵏⴰⵡⴰⵢⵜ) — the standardised Amazigh variety codified by IRCAM (Institut Royal de la Culture Amazighe) and an official language of Morocco since 2011. Written in Neo-Tifinagh (IRCAM variant, Unicode block Tifinagh), which is a true alphabet: vowels are written with their own letters, not diacritics. Regular, essentially one-to-one letter→phoneme mapping. Emphatic (pharyngealised) consonants ⴹ ⵕ ⵚ ⵟ ⵥ are distinct letters. ⵓ is /u/ as a vowel and /w/ in glide position; ⵡ is unambiguously /w/. Labiovelars ⴳⵯ /ɡʷ/ and ⴽⵯ /kʷ/ are written with the labialisation mark ⵯ. Tifinagh is unicase.",
  "orthography_standard": {
